<h2>Blockquotes</h2>

<p>Use <code>&gt;</code> to create blockquotes. Nest them for multi-level quotes.</p>

<CodeBlock lang="markdown" code={codeBlockquotes} />

<h2>Tables</h2>

<p>Create tables using pipes <code>|</code> and hyphens <code>-</code>. Align columns with colons.</p>

<CodeBlock lang="markdown" code={codeTables} />

<ul>
  <li><code>:---</code> — left-aligned (default)</li>
  <li><code>:---:</code> — center-aligned</li>
  <li><code>---:</code> — right-aligned</li>
</ul>

<h2>Horizontal rules</h2>

<p>Create horizontal dividers with three or more hyphens, asterisks, or underscores on their own line.</p>

<CodeBlock lang="markdown" code={codeHR} />

<h2>Footnotes</h2>

<p>Footnotes allow you to add references without cluttering the main text. CodeInk supports GFM footnotes.</p>

<CodeBlock lang="markdown" code={codeFootnotes} />

<h2>GitHub-style alerts</h2>

<p>CodeInk supports GitHub-style alert blocks for callouts and admonitions.</p>

<CodeBlock lang="markdown" code={codeAlerts} />

<h2>Mermaid diagrams</h2>

<p>CodeInk renders <a href="/mermaid-diagrams-guide">Mermaid diagrams</a> directly in the preview. Use a fenced code block with the <code>mermaid</code> language identifier.</p>

<CodeBlock lang="markdown" code={codeMermaid} />

<h2>Math with KaTeX</h2>

<p>CodeInk supports <a href="/katex-math-guide">KaTeX math</a> expressions. Use single dollar signs for inline math and double dollar signs for display math.</p>

<CodeBlock lang="markdown" code={codeMath} />

